1
00:01:29,210 --> 00:01:34,910
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:37,780
[Episode 6]

3
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:41,080
All right, guys.

4
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:43,310
Let's look at this question.

5
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:46,150
As for this one,

6
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:48,880
I know some of you
still don't know how to solve it.

7
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:51,509
It is a bit difficult.

8
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:52,759
Mr. Gu,

9
00:01:53,509 --> 00:01:55,039
stop the class for a moment.

10
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:01,880
Your class caused this incident!

11
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:03,970
Mind you, I know who it was!

12
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:06,010
Whoever did it,

13
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,970
step forward right now!

14
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,940
You've got some nerve.

15
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:18,800
What? No one wants to admit it?

16
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:20,910
Fine.

17
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,190
I'll give this saboteur

18
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:27,750
one last chance.

19
00:02:28,510 --> 00:02:29,520
Step forward now,

20
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,300
and I'll be lenient.

21
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:34,870
If I have to check the handwriting
and figure out who did it,

22
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:35,940
whoever it is,

23
00:02:35,970 --> 00:02:37,770
they'll be expelled right away!

24
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:43,030
Director.

25
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,270
I posted them.

26
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:50,960
I knew it was you.

27
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:55,000
This just proves

28
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,650
that I was right about my judgment

29
00:02:56,650 --> 00:02:57,980
of your poor character.

30
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:00,080
Just wait to be expelled.

31
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:03,630
Wait, you're deceiving us again.

32
00:03:03,630 --> 00:03:05,240
Didn't you just say you'd be lenient?

33
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,240
For you, you'll be

34
00:03:07,690 --> 00:03:09,310
punished for multiple offenses.

35
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:10,110
Director Hou,

36
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,470
don't listen to Xiaoman's nonsense.

37
00:03:12,470 --> 00:03:13,790
I wrote those criticism posters.

38
00:03:13,790 --> 00:03:15,030
It has nothing to do with him.

39
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:15,680
Xia Lei!

40
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:17,840
You are still young.

41
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,760
Don't take the fall for someone else

42
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:20,430
out of loyalty.

43
00:03:20,430 --> 00:03:21,590
Mr. Gu, it really was me.

44
00:03:21,590 --> 00:03:22,870
If you don't believe it,
look at the handwriting.

45
00:03:22,870 --> 00:03:23,520
L-Look.

46
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:25,079
It definitely wasn't him. It was me.

47
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:25,740
You shut up!

48
00:03:26,030 --> 00:03:27,910
Look, look at this handwriting.

49
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:29,860
And... And that... that flyers were

50
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:31,950
also... also put up by me.

51
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,120
It has nothing to do with anyone...

52
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:33,920
Director Hou!

53
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:35,310
I can testify that Xia Lei is lying.

54
00:03:35,310 --> 00:03:36,100
I'm not lying.

55
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,100
You are.

56
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:38,250
See? Huh?

57
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,480
Do you know who did it?

58
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,340
Anyway, he didn't do it alone.

59
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:45,190
He did write the posters.

60
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:46,829
But I printed the flyers.

61
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,120
We put them up together.

62
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,360
It has nothing to do with Xiaoman.

63
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:50,530
He wasn't part of it at all.

64
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:51,840
It has nothing to do with either of them.

65
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,100
Who else was involved?

66
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:54,680
Me.

67
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:56,040
Oh, my God.

68
00:03:56,710 --> 00:03:57,430
Meng Ge?

69
00:03:58,230 --> 00:03:59,110
What did you do?

70
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,480
I didn't do anything.

71
00:04:01,890 --> 00:04:02,680
Why did you stand up

72
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,140
if you didn't do anything?

73
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,270
I leaked

74
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:07,950
the poster's content to them.

75
00:04:11,310 --> 00:04:12,500
Get the parents of the three of you

76
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:13,300
to the school.

77
00:04:13,870 --> 00:04:15,070
It's four, Director.

78
00:04:18,269 --> 00:04:19,000
You guys

79
00:04:19,490 --> 00:04:21,089
really are out of your minds.

80
00:04:21,269 --> 00:04:23,530
Grades are the first priority right now.

81
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,880
Sit down and get back to class.

82
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:28,010
I'll talk to your parents after class!

83
00:04:29,870 --> 00:04:32,650
[Teaching Building]

84
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:39,430
Mrs. Tong.

85
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:42,460
You...

86
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,270
Where did you get the nerve?

87
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:47,070
What if you get officially punished?

88
00:04:47,070 --> 00:04:47,920
Go... Hurry up.

89
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,120
G-Go apologize to the Director.

90
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,260
See if he'll forgive you.

91
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:51,060
I'm not going.

92
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,270
Mrs. Tong, Mrs. Tong.

93
00:04:52,270 --> 00:04:53,950
I'm not going. I won't go!

94
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,640
It was the Director's fault.

95
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:57,370
I have nothing to hide. W-Why should I go?

96
00:04:57,370 --> 00:04:58,600
N-Nothing to hide?

97
00:04:58,630 --> 00:05:00,360
If so, why didn't you put them up

98
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:01,630
during the day?

99
00:05:01,630 --> 00:05:02,290
Move aside.

100
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:04,600
Why are you yelling at the kid?

101
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,240
Huh?

102
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:07,070
You never shut up.

103
00:05:08,510 --> 00:05:09,570
Just stay out of it.

104
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:13,310
Mr. Ding.

105
00:05:15,510 --> 00:05:17,040
Do you think you were wrong?

106
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:18,480
I...

107
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:20,560
I-I was wrong.

108
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,160
Wrong about what?

109
00:05:22,270 --> 00:05:23,330
Why were you wrong?

110
00:05:23,870 --> 00:05:25,270
If there was a mistake...

111
00:05:26,870 --> 00:05:28,170
it's that you only posted them
at the school

112
00:05:28,170 --> 00:05:30,100
and not at the plant headquarters.

113
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,270
If I were you,
I'd have plastered them everywhere.

114
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:34,200
I'd even have covered the ceiling.

115
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,680
See? Mr. Ding's really something.

116
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,070
How silver-tongued he is!

117
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:39,070
What a speech!

118
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,290
Dad.

119
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,930
Made a fuss, huh?

120
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:03,960
It's already happened.

121
00:06:04,190 --> 00:06:05,960
The school will definitely
issue a punishment.

122
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:09,300
But we can't accept a penalty mark

123
00:06:09,370 --> 00:06:10,770
on the permanent record.

124
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:12,270
Chief Engineer Yan is right.

125
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:14,130
We absolutely can't accept that.

126
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,380
So we're all on the same page.

127
00:06:22,180 --> 00:06:23,980
I'll do the talking when we go in.

128
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:24,680
You...

129
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,720
Should I talk or not?

130
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:29,120
Just listen.

131
00:06:29,310 --> 00:06:30,800
W-What does this mean?

132
00:06:31,370 --> 00:06:32,310
I have worked diligently,

133
00:06:32,310 --> 00:06:34,270
dedicating my whole life to education.

134
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:36,510
I may not have
abundant students everywhere, right?

135
00:06:36,510 --> 00:06:38,130
But give me credit for my hard work,
if not my achievements.

136
00:06:38,130 --> 00:06:39,630
This was the first time someone

137
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:40,600
put up criticism posters about me.

138
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,000
In the future, my work...

139
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:45,159
It's been a while since we last met,

140
00:06:45,159 --> 00:06:45,960
Director Hou.

141
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,120
Hello, Director.

142
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,190
-Come on, sit down, please.
-Okay.

143
00:06:51,190 --> 00:06:52,320
Have a seat, please.

144
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,980
I was just outside,

145
00:06:56,230 --> 00:06:58,030
and I heard everything you said.

146
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:01,120
Indeed, after all these years,

147
00:07:01,650 --> 00:07:03,450
we all know your reputation

148
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:05,240
in the school.

149
00:07:05,340 --> 00:07:05,980
Right?

150
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:10,310
Your achievements and credits are

151
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,060
evident to all.

152
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:17,220
But this incident has already happened.

153
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:20,670
I don't know
how the school plans to handle it.

154
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,800
This incident has exerted

155
00:07:23,830 --> 00:07:25,830
a terrible influence on the school.

156
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:28,480
We must deal with it seriously

157
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,940
to make an example of them.

158
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:31,860
Director, please don't.

159
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:33,870
We f-failed to educate our child well.

160
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:35,870
I'll have them come
apologize to you right now.

161
00:07:35,870 --> 00:07:36,560
Tong,

162
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:39,430
I don't think this is
about apologizing at all.

163
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:40,190
Sit down.

164
00:07:42,890 --> 00:07:46,280
I believe
the school will handle this carefully,

165
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:49,380
because it concerns the children's future.

166
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:50,470
Furthermore,

167
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:53,550
the school will also
consider its own interests,

168
00:07:53,550 --> 00:07:54,140
right?

169
00:07:54,170 --> 00:07:56,090
If this investigation continues

170
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:57,550
and the higher-ups learn that...

171
00:07:57,550 --> 00:08:00,080
The content
written above is all fabricated.

172
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,630
It is not true at all.

173
00:08:02,670 --> 00:08:05,110
We take pilot recruitment very seriously.

174
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,360
But in our work,

175
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,380
slip-ups are inevitable.

176
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,920
Where is the slip-up?

177
00:08:10,930 --> 00:08:11,790
What slip-ups?

178
00:08:13,510 --> 00:08:14,370
Sirs and madam,

179
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,870
before you came in,

180
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:17,430
I already admitted to Director Hou

181
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:18,630
that I made a mistake.

182
00:08:18,890 --> 00:08:20,760
Here, I would also like to formally

183
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:23,040
apologize to you all.

184
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,050
This is truly a misunderstanding.

185
00:08:25,310 --> 00:08:26,710
As the head teacher,

186
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:28,600
I didn't deliver the message properly.

187
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,510
As a result,
the pilot recruitment information

188
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:32,110
did not reach every student,

189
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:35,169
causing today's misunderstanding.

190
00:08:37,770 --> 00:08:38,580
Yan,

191
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,480
the situation is pretty clear now.

192
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,510
It has nothing to do with the children.

193
00:08:43,510 --> 00:08:44,570
So why punish them?

194
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,870
Xiaoman, take the two of them back.

195
00:08:46,890 --> 00:08:47,610
Ding,

196
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:49,750
I disagree with you.

197
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:52,410
I think we should take this opportunity

198
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,900
to teach them a good lesson

199
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:56,190
and let them know
the importance of following rules

200
00:08:56,190 --> 00:08:58,070
and seeing the big picture.

201
00:08:58,510 --> 00:08:59,970
What happened? What is it?

202
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:01,270
I don't know.

203
00:09:01,870 --> 00:09:03,200
I don't think he called me.

204
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,270
That startled me.

205
00:09:08,090 --> 00:09:09,570
Look at this mess. Well...

206
00:09:10,140 --> 00:09:11,800
It was supposed to be my issue,

207
00:09:12,020 --> 00:09:13,820
but you two were dragged into it.

208
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:17,500
Thank you for your understanding,
Chief Engineer Yan.

209
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:21,720
In handling this matter, the school

210
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:24,870
will definitely minimize the impact

211
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:27,530
and won't let it affect
the children's future.

212
00:09:27,530 --> 00:09:29,440
"Won't let it affect
the children's future."

213
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,440
That's well said.

214
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:33,480
Well, then...

215
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:36,790
About Xiaoman's pilot recruitment...

216
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:38,160
Here.

217
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:41,480
Do you have
the Pilot Recruitment Office's number?

218
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,120
Yes, we do.

219
00:09:42,430 --> 00:09:43,910
Here, Director. Come on.

220
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,390
Director, this one.

221
00:09:45,390 --> 00:09:46,540
I'll call them right now.

222
00:09:46,540 --> 00:09:47,350
Right now.

223
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:49,750
Immediate action.

224
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:52,160
Pilot Recruitment Office.

225
00:09:58,150 --> 00:10:00,030
You three, come in.

226
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,860
Director, I'm going to announce it.

227
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:06,370
Okay.

228
00:10:09,390 --> 00:10:10,320
Stand straight.

229
00:10:11,210 --> 00:10:14,010
I'm going to announce
the disciplinary decision.

230
00:10:14,510 --> 00:10:16,630
This incident
stemmed from a misunderstanding,

231
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:18,870
but Xia Lei and Xiaodan's behaviors

232
00:10:18,910 --> 00:10:20,840
still caused damage to the school.

233
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,520
The school leaders and parents have agreed

234
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:25,600
to punish Xia Lei and Xiaodan

235
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:29,180
by making them
clean the teaching building for a month.

236
00:10:29,910 --> 00:10:30,640
That's fair.

237
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:31,660
As for Xiaoman,

238
00:10:32,190 --> 00:10:34,150
the Director will contact
the Pilot Recruitment Office

239
00:10:34,150 --> 00:10:36,610
to add your name
to the recommendation list.

240
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:38,770
Make one more call
and see if anyone answers.

241
00:10:38,770 --> 00:10:40,030
Okay, I'll call again.

242
00:10:40,630 --> 00:10:41,440
Calm down.

243
00:10:45,620 --> 00:10:46,310
Hello?

244
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:49,090
Is this the Pilot Recruitment Office?

245
00:10:49,830 --> 00:10:53,960
This is Mr. Hou from Western Tiecheng
Dongfang Affiliated Middle School.

246
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:54,910
Yes, yes.

247
00:10:56,050 --> 00:10:57,970
Here's the thing. Our school

248
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:01,020
would like to recommend
an additional student.

249
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:02,050
He's excellent,

250
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,240
in great shape,

251
00:11:03,550 --> 00:11:04,350
and very tall.

252
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:06,900
His height?

253
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,480
1.87 meters.

254
00:11:09,420 --> 00:11:10,820
1.9 meters with shoes on.

255
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,670
He is 1.87 meters tall.

256
00:11:14,330 --> 00:11:14,970
Pardon?

257
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,730
So that's the case.

258
00:11:20,670 --> 00:11:22,960
Okay, yeah, I see.

259
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,870
Thank you.

260
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:27,720
Goodbye.

261
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:28,960
Get ready.

262
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:30,710
To fill out the form?

263
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,420
Let's go! Time to take off!

264
00:11:32,870 --> 00:11:34,130
You're over the limit.

265
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,200
Over the limit by 2 centimeters.

266
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:39,960
So being tall is a problem?

267
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,810
With t-this height,

268
00:11:40,810 --> 00:11:42,800
he'd e-even be leading the Honor Guard.

269
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:43,710
Hear me out.

270
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,390
For male pilots,

271
00:11:45,670 --> 00:11:48,380
the maximum height is 1.85 meters.

272
00:11:48,820 --> 00:11:50,300
Why did you grow so tall?

273
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:51,880
Well...

274
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,750
I grew up eating everyone's food.

275
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:55,120
Eating here today, there tomorrow.

276
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,360
Mrs. Tong's cooking is amazing,

277
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:58,870
and Mr. Ding feeds me
like livestock every day.

278
00:11:58,870 --> 00:11:59,630
Stop yapping.

279
00:11:59,630 --> 00:12:01,720
"Mr. Ding," "Mr. Ding."
Are you blaming us?

280
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,790
You must've secretly eaten
abundant feed yourself.

281
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:05,300
Y-You call me over to eat every day...

282
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:05,990
Xiaoman,

283
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,320
I really tried to help you sincerely.

284
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:10,560
But it's okay.

285
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:12,360
All roads lead to Rome.

286
00:12:12,910 --> 00:12:14,840
With your build and height,

287
00:12:15,390 --> 00:12:16,670
getting into a sports school is

288
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:17,710
also a good choice.

289
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:19,720
Getting into a sports school isn't
the same as flying a plane.

290
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:20,270
Alright.

291
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:21,930
Director Hou is right.

292
00:12:22,870 --> 00:12:25,000
All roads lead to Rome, right?

293
00:12:25,580 --> 00:12:26,430
So,

294
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:28,800
shouldn't we let the kids
go back to class first?

295
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:31,040
Right. You guys go to class now.

296
00:12:32,390 --> 00:12:33,650
-Go back now.
-Go back.

297
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,980
We went to all that trouble

298
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,260
for nothing in the end.

299
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:46,360
Xiaoman, do you have any regrets?

300
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:51,910
No. Didn't you hear?

301
00:12:52,170 --> 00:12:53,900
Even if my name were submitted,

302
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,810
I wouldn't have been selected.

303
00:12:56,830 --> 00:12:59,380
It's okay. But after today, I realized

304
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:00,910
what matters most.

305
00:13:01,270 --> 00:13:03,480
My friends matter most.

306
00:13:03,660 --> 00:13:04,690
No matter what happens,

307
00:13:04,690 --> 00:13:06,890
my friends will always stand by my side.

308
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,320
Just like what I read in that book.

309
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,480
"Gold is like dirt

310
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:13,080
compared to priceless friends."

311
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,320
"Friends who are worth 1,000 gold."

312
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:15,460
That means "priceless," right?

313
00:13:15,460 --> 00:13:16,990
Forget about gold and dirt.

314
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:18,990
Have you forgotten our poem?

315
00:13:19,410 --> 00:13:20,690
"I am a kapok tree.

316
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:22,250
As trees,

317
00:13:22,270 --> 00:13:23,550
we stand together."

318
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:25,460
Okay.

319
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:26,870
Xiaoman,

320
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,280
give some thought

321
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:31,910
to the sports school
Director Hou mentioned.

322
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:32,750
Think it over.

323
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:35,550
They're back! There they come!

324
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,050
How did it go?

325
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:40,640
How did it go?

326
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:41,840
What did they say?

327
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:46,240
He didn't get selected.

328
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:49,080
It's okay, Xiaoman. Don't be discouraged.

329
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:51,510
Whether it's
reading a self-criticism on stage or what,

330
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:53,100
you must count me in.

331
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,280
Really, Meng Ge?

332
00:13:57,910 --> 00:14:00,040
You're really willing
to share weal and woe with us?

333
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:02,470
Yes, of course! We are friends.

334
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:04,270
I can't let you guys
steal all the spotlight.

335
00:14:04,270 --> 00:14:04,960
Great.

336
00:14:05,870 --> 00:14:06,550
Okay.

337
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:08,390
We are

338
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:09,910
not expelled.

339
00:14:10,110 --> 00:14:13,510
Our punishment is to clean
the teaching building for a month.

340
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:15,890
Good job, Yan Xiaodan.

341
00:14:15,910 --> 00:14:17,070
I still have things to do. I'm leaving.

342
00:14:17,070 --> 00:14:18,120
Don't go, Meng Ge.

343
00:14:18,590 --> 00:14:20,650
Didn't we agree to share weal and woe?

344
00:14:52,420 --> 00:14:56,020
[Celebrate the Return of Hong Kong]

345
00:14:59,270 --> 00:15:00,320
Why hasn't Sun Lulu

346
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:02,650
come to ask me about math problems lately?

347
00:15:04,910 --> 00:15:06,770
She solved her problems herself.

348
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:07,890
What do you mean?

349
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:11,840
Can't you tell

350
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:12,720
that she asked you questions

351
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:14,780
just to see Zhang Xiaoman every time?

352
00:15:14,810 --> 00:15:16,360
Zhang Xiaoman, that fool,

353
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:18,960
delivered a letter for someone
without signing the sender's name,

354
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,960
which made Sun Lulu misunderstand.

355
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,200
Now it's done for.

356
00:15:22,550 --> 00:15:24,080
Sun Lulu knows everything.

357
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:26,280
So she's too embarrassed to come again.

358
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,910
What? You don't believe me?

359
00:15:31,910 --> 00:15:33,360
Xiaoman told me himself.

360
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,910
Why would Xiaoman explain that to you?

361
00:15:35,910 --> 00:15:36,790
Was it because

362
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:39,050
you got jealous?

363
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,600
Why would I get jealous?

364
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:41,140
I...

365
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:46,850
I just couldn't bear
to see that girl getting the wrong idea.

366
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:49,150
Fine.

367
00:15:49,980 --> 00:15:52,110
It's best if you don't misunderstand.

368
00:15:54,510 --> 00:15:55,310
A little more.

369
00:15:56,010 --> 00:15:57,070
Move a little more.

370
00:15:58,050 --> 00:15:59,270
Look, a bit higher and a bit lower.

371
00:15:59,270 --> 00:16:00,720
Let's work it out. Lower.

372
00:16:02,950 --> 00:16:04,470
Right here! Nice!

373
00:16:04,910 --> 00:16:05,770
Stay still.

374
00:16:05,910 --> 00:16:06,750
-Okay.
-It's here. Right here.

375
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:07,120
Okay.

376
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:07,870
Keep it in this direction.

377
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:08,810
Good. We have a signal.

378
00:16:08,810 --> 00:16:09,240
Great.

379
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:10,840
We have a signal.

380
00:16:11,150 --> 00:16:11,720
There's a signal.

381
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,790
Xiaoman! Where are you going?

382
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:15,510
Don't leave me alone here...

383
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:16,230
I...

384
00:16:17,780 --> 00:16:18,980
Signal's connected.

385
00:16:21,010 --> 00:16:22,270
You've started eating?

386
00:16:22,270 --> 00:16:23,080
Red sausage!

387
00:16:23,910 --> 00:16:24,550
We've got that thing here.

388
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:25,340
Looks delicious.

389
00:16:25,340 --> 00:16:27,320
The thing Dongdong brought from home.

390
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,380
Chocolate... Chocolate champagne.

391
00:16:29,550 --> 00:16:31,030
Champagne? Alcohol?

392
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,430
I don't know. Chocolate.

393
00:16:32,670 --> 00:16:34,270
That should be a soft drink, I guess.

394
00:16:34,270 --> 00:16:35,060
Dongdong!

395
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:36,550
Chocolate champagne.

396
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:37,810
Hurry up. I'll open it.

397
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:38,960
Why didn't you wait for me?

398
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:40,420
Aren't we waiting for you?

399
00:16:41,410 --> 00:16:43,690
-Open it. Let's drink.
-Open it!

400
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,220
Can your teeth really handle it?

401
00:16:45,220 --> 00:16:46,320
You have your own "bottle opener."

402
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:48,320
There are cups! Come on, top them up.

403
00:16:48,470 --> 00:16:49,960
Pour it. Smells pretty good.

404
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:51,790
Let's substitute drinks for wine today.

405
00:16:51,790 --> 00:16:52,280
Cheers!

406
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,440
Come on. Cheers.

407
00:16:53,630 --> 00:16:54,550
Cheers!

408
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:56,260
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

409
00:17:00,630 --> 00:17:02,160
I'll show you a magic trick.

410
00:17:02,470 --> 00:17:02,990
What?

411
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:03,810
A magic trick.

412
00:17:03,810 --> 00:17:04,480
Right here?

413
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:05,960
Just a second.

414
00:17:06,349 --> 00:17:07,310
Where are you going?

415
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:09,109
He's going to do the magic trick.

416
00:17:09,290 --> 00:17:11,020
These pickles are way too sour.

417
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,160
Is this your magic trick?

418
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,130
You conjured this up?

419
00:17:16,130 --> 00:17:17,109
Like a big bathtub.

420
00:17:17,109 --> 00:17:18,109
Are you going to take a bath?

421
00:17:18,109 --> 00:17:19,170
What are you doing?

422
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,000
A magic trick!

423
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:22,200
Come on. Come here.

424
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:23,310
What is it?

425
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,170
I poured too much water. It's too heavy.

426
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:26,480
What?
Are you going to scrub someone's back?

427
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,140
Stand on it.

428
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,480
Are you ready?

429
00:17:31,110 --> 00:17:31,640
Behold.

430
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:33,550
Look.

431
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:34,740
Watch closely.

432
00:17:39,310 --> 00:17:40,970
Come on. Let's block the wind.

433
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:42,790
-Let's block the wind.
-We have to block it.

434
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:43,650
Block the wind.

435
00:17:44,510 --> 00:17:45,910
Block it. Block the wind.

436
00:17:56,030 --> 00:17:56,840
So high!

437
00:17:59,030 --> 00:18:01,030
-This one is big! Amazing!
-This...

438
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:02,720
Does it look great inside?

439
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,350
It looks great! Especially from inside!

440
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:05,310
It's completely different.

441
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:06,830
So, what do you think?

442
00:18:06,850 --> 00:18:07,550
Impressive.

443
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:09,510
Am I, Zhang Xiaoman, amazing?

444
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:12,200
Meng Ge. Meng Ge, you...

445
00:18:13,110 --> 00:18:14,110
Why don't you try?

446
00:18:26,220 --> 00:18:27,080
Go, go ahead.

447
00:18:27,110 --> 00:18:28,510
Is it beautiful inside?

448
00:18:29,350 --> 00:18:30,010
Yeah, it is.

449
00:18:33,060 --> 00:18:34,860
What's wrong? Don't you like it?

450
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:36,350
No.

451
00:18:37,460 --> 00:18:38,390
It's too unreal.

452
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:40,900
And I don't dare to like it.

453
00:18:42,510 --> 00:18:43,640
It won't last at all.

454
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,010
But... But it's so beautiful.

455
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,790
With your build,
I can't find the right angle.

456
00:18:47,790 --> 00:18:48,510
What do you mean, Wang Dongdong?

457
00:18:48,510 --> 00:18:49,960
No, no. I mean...

458
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,000
Get up!

459
00:18:51,270 --> 00:18:51,750
Look at those two.

460
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:52,590
Stop talking!

461
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:55,150
Sometimes I quite envy them.

462
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:57,620
They live in this soap bubble,

463
00:18:58,110 --> 00:19:00,170
never having seen the outside world.

464
00:19:00,550 --> 00:19:01,720
They don't know

465
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:04,910
that the colorfulness of life is

466
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:07,470
just a reflection of the outside world.

467
00:19:10,030 --> 00:19:12,030
But soap bubbles are easily broken.

468
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:16,280
Are you saying
our plant is like a soap bubble?

469
00:19:17,420 --> 00:19:19,550
Our plant made this year's fireworks.

470
00:19:20,070 --> 00:19:21,070
Did you know that?

471
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:23,070
My dad told me that.

472
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:25,810
But our plant
used to make smokeless powder.

473
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:30,290
After switching
from military to civilian production,

474
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:32,020
what future do we have?

475
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:36,550
Why would you think about that?

476
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:39,750
Just tell me if you think
that moment was beautiful or not.

477
00:19:40,430 --> 00:19:42,030
It was literally a flash in the pan.

478
00:19:42,030 --> 00:19:43,430
Was it beautiful? Was it?

479
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:45,790
Was it great?

480
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,720
I can't say it wasn't.

481
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:50,400
See? A double negative makes a positive.

482
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:51,310
So it was beautiful.

483
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:53,270
Even if it's fleeting, it's beautiful.

484
00:19:53,270 --> 00:19:54,310
Yeah, yeah, beautiful.

485
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:56,070
It's beautiful. Come on.

486
00:19:57,030 --> 00:19:58,550
Starting now,

487
00:19:58,550 --> 00:20:01,400
we are broadcasting
this grand ceremony live.

488
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,680
-Take it slow.
-Be careful, Lulu.

489
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:03,140
Come on.

490
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:04,510
Hong Kong's return is

491
00:20:04,580 --> 00:20:07,780
the long-cherished call
in the hearts of Chinese people.

492
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:09,640
Hong Kong's return is

493
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:12,400
the shared expectation
of all Chinese people.

494
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:13,220
Let's go.

495
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:16,110
Over 150 years of this long journey,

496
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:19,310
over 150 years
of these unforgettable times.

497
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:20,550
Today,

498
00:20:20,550 --> 00:20:23,790
Hong Kong has finally returned
to the motherland's embrace.

499
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:26,390
More than 6,000,000
Hong Kong compatriots are

500
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:28,360
finally free from colonial rule,

501
00:20:28,390 --> 00:20:29,310
entering

502
00:20:29,310 --> 00:20:31,350
a new era where they hold sway

503
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:32,750
over their own destiny.

504
00:20:38,790 --> 00:20:39,590
It's returned.

505
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:40,240
Cheers.

506
00:20:40,270 --> 00:20:42,270
-It's back! Welcome back!
-Cheers!

507
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,240
I'm out!

508
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,880
-Get a bottle.
-Pour it.

509
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,480
Get a bottle. Here, Dongdong.

510
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,400
-Come on.
-Thank you.

511
00:20:52,030 --> 00:20:53,240
Fireworks!

512
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:56,240
Fireworks bloomed
in the sky for just an instant,

513
00:20:57,720 --> 00:21:00,750
yet the plant's roar had lasted for years.

514
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:03,550
On a summer night in 1997,

515
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,640
dazzling fireworks

516
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,290
lit up half the sky over Western Tiecheng.

517
00:21:09,550 --> 00:21:11,440
People looked up,

518
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:14,640
grinding the calluses on their palms,

519
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:16,680
through the countless days
and nights to come,

520
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:18,140
into longings and dreams,

521
00:21:18,790 --> 00:21:20,450
into companionship and hope.

522
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,010
Fireworks bloomed,

523
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:26,720
illuminating our youthful faces
time and time again.

524
00:21:27,590 --> 00:21:29,190
We cheered with jubilation,

525
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:32,210
smiling as we embraced
the upcoming prosperity.

526
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:34,880
We made wishes about our hometown,

527
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:35,880
about each other,

528
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:37,750
and about the future.

529
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:41,880
But we never noticed
the gears of time were

530
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,880
already silently turning toward the bend.

531
00:21:58,030 --> 00:21:59,890
Come on, Mr. Li. This way, please.

532
00:22:00,070 --> 00:22:01,200
Take a look, please.

533
00:22:02,790 --> 00:22:05,640
You've opened
so many pool halls in Tiecheng.

534
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:07,440
You surely know the market well.

535
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:09,410
And our asking price is really low.

536
00:22:09,550 --> 00:22:11,880
You'll definitely make a profit
if you buy it.

537
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:14,200
There are barely any customers here.

538
00:22:14,980 --> 00:22:16,640
Well, it's not peak hours yet.

539
00:22:17,030 --> 00:22:18,560
Once it is, it'll be packed.

540
00:22:19,070 --> 00:22:19,670
Oh, right.

541
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:21,720
Look at our cues.

542
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:22,750
These are

543
00:22:22,790 --> 00:22:24,350
a new batch we got 2 months ago,

544
00:22:24,350 --> 00:22:25,350
of great quality.

545
00:22:25,350 --> 00:22:28,070
And those lights on the wall.

546
00:22:28,070 --> 00:22:29,110
You can check them out later

547
00:22:29,110 --> 00:22:30,480
to see how good they are.

548
00:22:32,070 --> 00:22:34,110
Okay. The equipment is good.

549
00:22:34,270 --> 00:22:34,790
Right?

550
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:35,830
Later on,

551
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:38,720
tear down
those broken machines in the back.

552
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:40,380
We can fit in a few more tables.

553
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:41,480
And repaint the walls.

554
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,480
This is way too old now.

555
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:43,030
Okay, okay.

556
00:22:43,030 --> 00:22:44,240
Once you take it over, you're the boss.

557
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:45,110
You can do whatever you want.

558
00:22:45,110 --> 00:22:45,440
Okay.

559
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:46,530
Wait a minute.

560
00:22:47,830 --> 00:22:48,590
Mr. Li.

561
00:22:49,420 --> 00:22:51,110
You might not have read this contract.

562
00:22:51,110 --> 00:22:52,710
It's written very clearly here.

563
00:22:52,710 --> 00:22:53,800
If you want to take over this place,

564
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:55,330
you can't make any changes.

565
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:56,110
Look at you.

566
00:22:56,110 --> 00:22:57,610
You didn't tell me

567
00:22:57,640 --> 00:22:59,000
about this situation earlier!

568
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,000
That's not what we mean.

569
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,790
What's wrong? This is our plant.

570
00:23:01,790 --> 00:23:03,640
We want to keep it as it was.

571
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:07,080
You think you can keep it
just because you want to?

572
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:09,360
Still living in the past?

573
00:23:10,350 --> 00:23:12,030
Look at the reality, bro!

574
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,370
What do you mean?

575
00:23:13,370 --> 00:23:15,040
I heard people saying

576
00:23:15,070 --> 00:23:16,670
that people in your plant are

577
00:23:17,030 --> 00:23:18,070
all leaving.

578
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:20,480
I'm even worried

579
00:23:21,310 --> 00:23:24,370
that no one will be playing
in the pool hall in a couple of days.

580
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:25,180
To be honest,

581
00:23:25,210 --> 00:23:27,240
were it not for the low price you offered,

582
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:29,550
I wouldn't even take over this dump.

583
00:23:30,570 --> 00:23:32,370
In this case, just don't take it.

584
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:34,070
Right?

585
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:36,410
Hey, Wang Tieda.

586
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,750
Are you fooling me?

587
00:23:40,270 --> 00:23:41,400
Why would I fool you?

588
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:44,030
I just don't want
to sell it anymore, okay?

589
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:45,880
The tools you use to make a living

590
00:23:46,110 --> 00:23:47,970
have all turned into scrap metal!

591
00:23:48,350 --> 00:23:50,240
And you're still acting tough with me?

592
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:53,500
You still think the East Chemical Plant
can be great again?

593
00:23:57,110 --> 00:23:58,350
That's funny.

594
00:24:00,110 --> 00:24:02,440
About what our factory has become,

595
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:04,590
is it up to you?

596
00:24:05,270 --> 00:24:06,400
Or up to you?

597
00:24:06,550 --> 00:24:07,210
Xiaoman...

598
00:24:07,550 --> 00:24:08,720
Or up to you guys?

599
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:12,130
Exactly. Tiecheng has only been doing well
for a few years,

600
00:24:12,130 --> 00:24:13,720
and you already dare to challenge us here.

601
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:14,780
Have you forgotten

602
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:17,270
when you used to come here
to collect scrap?

603
00:24:17,270 --> 00:24:19,920
Now you're looking down on us like a snob.

604
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,340
Who are you calling a snob?

605
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:23,930
It's you.

606
00:24:24,380 --> 00:24:25,590
Stop yelling here.

607
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:27,960
We haven't signed a contract.

608
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:29,160
And you haven't paid.

609
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:31,560
If you want to play this game,

610
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:32,830
I'll show you

611
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:34,640
how united our plant is.

612
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:41,880
Fine, Wang Tieda.

613
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:43,970
I'll remember you guys.

614
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:46,960
This isn't over.

615
00:24:48,790 --> 00:24:49,320
Let's go.

616
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:51,200
See yourself out.

617
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:54,400
W-Who does he think he is?

618
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:56,200
You don't want to sell it anymore?

619
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:57,660
I don't want to sell to him.

620
00:24:59,070 --> 00:25:00,190
He scared the balls away.

621
00:25:00,190 --> 00:25:00,700
Bro,

622
00:25:01,550 --> 00:25:04,030
will we still sell this place
in the future?

623
00:25:04,530 --> 00:25:06,010
Of course we will sell it.

624
00:25:06,380 --> 00:25:08,010
But I decide who I sell to.

625
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:42,640
Take a break.

626
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,930
You need to balance study and rest,
don't you?

627
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,880
I'm doing a practice test.

628
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:48,960
I'm timing myself.

629
00:25:49,550 --> 00:25:50,590
Tell Mom

630
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:52,640
that I'm not eating
or drinking anything right now.

631
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,570
Let's talk about it after I'm done.

632
00:26:00,070 --> 00:26:00,640
Okay.

633
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:07,290
Look, look at it.

634
00:26:07,310 --> 00:26:08,440
Why are all your fish

635
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:10,480
so spiritless today?

636
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:11,000
Look.

637
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,830
You need to pump some oxygen.

638
00:26:12,830 --> 00:26:14,110
I'm buying this to keep my child healthy.

639
00:26:14,110 --> 00:26:15,480
I can't let him get sick because of it.

640
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:16,340
It's not fresh.

641
00:26:16,550 --> 00:26:18,240
Miss, that's impossible.

642
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,640
You always buy fish here.

643
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:21,970
When have I ever cheated you
with bad fish?

644
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:24,830
You must have
stocked up on pit-farmed fish.

645
00:26:24,830 --> 00:26:26,130
The one I cooked last time

646
00:26:26,130 --> 00:26:27,160
tasted so muddy.

647
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:27,980
Look at this.

648
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:28,420
Wait.

649
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:29,370
I'm feeding it to my child.

650
00:26:29,370 --> 00:26:31,040
It has to be purely natural.

651
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:33,240
Look how lively this fish is.

652
00:26:33,950 --> 00:26:34,890
Tong Guizhen,

653
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,710
are you done?

654
00:26:36,830 --> 00:26:37,880
It's just eating fish.

655
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:38,350
What?

656
00:26:38,370 --> 00:26:39,440
In the whole East Chemical Plant,

657
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:41,610
is your son the only one
worthy of eating fish?

658
00:26:41,610 --> 00:26:43,240
Hey, w-watch your mouth.

659
00:26:43,270 --> 00:26:44,540
What does my son eating fish

660
00:26:44,540 --> 00:26:46,350
have to do with you?

661
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,270
Besides,

662
00:26:47,300 --> 00:26:49,440
my son will get a recommended admission
to Peking University.

663
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:50,880
So what if he eats a good fish?

664
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:52,140
Is that too much to ask?

665
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:55,960
I remember

666
00:26:56,030 --> 00:26:58,720
the last time our plant
had a Peking University student was

667
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,920
when Halley's Comet visited Earth.

668
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:04,350
I'd like to see
what kind of spectacle will appear

669
00:27:04,350 --> 00:27:06,010
in the sky this time next year.

670
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:09,310
You are just jealous of my child.

671
00:27:09,310 --> 00:27:10,400
But it's pointless.

672
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:11,240
Listen,

673
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:13,030
Xia Lei will surely
pass the exam and study outside.

674
00:27:13,030 --> 00:27:14,240
When he gets to the big city,

675
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:15,680
he can eat whatever he wants

676
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:16,880
from the sea or the lake.

677
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:17,590
Yeah, yeah.

678
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:19,160
Here, this one? Good.

679
00:27:19,400 --> 00:27:20,200
Look.

680
00:27:20,480 --> 00:27:21,830
Look at her mindset.

681
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:23,480
That's why they say

682
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:25,680
their family is "rich in spirit."

683
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:26,550
Who are you talking about?

684
00:27:26,550 --> 00:27:27,880
What is "rich in spirit"?

685
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:28,400
It's about you.

686
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,590
Why are your words so unpleasant?

687
00:27:29,590 --> 00:27:30,640
-What do you mean?
-Who are you talking to?

688
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,880
What do you mean by "rich in spirit"?

689
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:33,070
Your family eats a fish,

690
00:27:33,070 --> 00:27:34,200
and you just won't shut up about it.

691
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,640
You know what? Some people

692
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:36,940
just can't stand seeing others do well.

693
00:27:36,940 --> 00:27:38,070
Forget about the fish!

694
00:27:38,070 --> 00:27:39,800
Could you please stop arguing?

695
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,880
How about this?
You two pick whatever you want,

696
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:42,880
and I'll round down the price.

697
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:43,210
Okay?

698
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:43,880
Yeah, look.

699
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,200
-Right.
-Since he said so.

700
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:46,030
I'm not eating.

701
00:27:46,030 --> 00:27:46,480
Wait.

702
00:27:46,590 --> 00:27:47,590
Eat it or not. I don't care.

703
00:27:47,590 --> 00:27:48,590
What is wrong with her?

704
00:27:48,590 --> 00:27:49,880
Use her discount for me.

705
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:50,540
No problem.

706
00:27:54,030 --> 00:27:55,290
T-This is quite fresh.

707
00:27:59,530 --> 00:28:00,340
Dad, I'm home.

708
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:04,520
Wash your hands. We'll eat soon.

709
00:28:04,740 --> 00:28:05,590
Where's Mom?

710
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,010
She got into a fight.

711
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:08,580
You two fought?

712
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:10,570
Nonsense. We didn't fight.

713
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:13,000
Come here!

714
00:28:14,030 --> 00:28:14,830
What's wrong?

715
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:18,610
She argued with someone
while buying groceries.

716
00:28:19,110 --> 00:28:19,970
She didn't win?

717
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:21,240
I didn't hear that.

718
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:23,170
What are you two whispering about?

719
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:24,480
The boy is hungry.

720
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:25,550
He asked when we'd eat.

721
00:28:25,550 --> 00:28:26,480
We'll eat soon.

722
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:28,240
Xia Lei.

723
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:30,480
Can you bring honor to me

724
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:32,110
and get the recommended admission?

725
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:34,070
How dare she call me
someone rich in spirit?

726
00:28:34,070 --> 00:28:34,880
Screw them.

727
00:28:35,070 --> 00:28:37,000
Come on. Make a promise to your mom.

728
00:28:37,500 --> 00:28:38,400
Mom, rest assured.

729
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:39,610
I'll definitely do well on the exam

730
00:28:39,610 --> 00:28:40,670
and make you proud.

731
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:42,620
Time to eat!

732
00:28:43,500 --> 00:28:44,060
Eat.

733
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:47,710
Here we go.

734
00:28:48,940 --> 00:28:49,550
One two.

735
00:28:52,110 --> 00:28:52,710
Straight.

736
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:54,740
Rear straight.

737
00:28:55,750 --> 00:28:56,550
One more time.

738
00:28:57,480 --> 00:28:58,010
One two.

739
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:00,590
One two.

740
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:02,080
One two.

741
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:03,480
Good.

742
00:29:04,350 --> 00:29:04,880
Left.

743
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:05,960
Left.

744
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:07,640
Left hook.

745
00:29:08,830 --> 00:29:09,690
Rear straight.

746
00:29:13,300 --> 00:29:14,590
Don't you dare push it!

747
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:20,880
Come on. Let's keep going.

748
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:22,140
It's fine. Ignore her.

749
00:29:27,270 --> 00:29:29,130
Forget about her. Come on, hit me.

750
00:29:29,270 --> 00:29:31,270
Straight punch. Use some force.

751
00:29:35,430 --> 00:29:36,150
Hit.

752
00:29:37,070 --> 00:29:39,070
Ignore her! Are you gonna hit or not?

753
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:44,850
Left.

754
00:29:58,100 --> 00:29:59,830
Practice by yourself for a bit.

755
00:30:02,940 --> 00:30:04,600
-Are you done?
-Stay out of it.

756
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:06,550
Are you done?

757
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:09,010
Will you take me away or not?

758
00:30:10,130 --> 00:30:11,790
How many times have I told you?

759
00:30:13,550 --> 00:30:15,010
Why won't you take me away?

760
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:17,350
How many times have I repeated it to you?

761
00:30:17,350 --> 00:30:18,400
I don't want you to mess around with me.

762
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:19,310
Nana's dad.

763
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:21,440
found a job for her in Shenyang,

764
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:22,440
but she doesn't want to go accept it.

765
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:24,040
She wants to go south with Da.

766
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:25,790
But Da

767
00:30:25,970 --> 00:30:27,660
wants her to keep the job

768
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:29,860
and wait until he's settled down.

769
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:33,360
Isn't he just afraid
she'll suffer if she goes south with him?

770
00:30:37,270 --> 00:30:38,870
But shouldn't people in love

771
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:40,200
stay together

772
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,530
no matter where they go?

773
00:30:52,500 --> 00:30:54,190
That's true. You're right.

774
00:31:29,590 --> 00:31:31,650
I'd like to emphasize the exam rules.

775
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:34,240
Don't cheat.

776
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,800
If you cheat, you will be caught.

777
00:31:36,830 --> 00:31:37,640
Is that clear?

778
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,200
Understood.

779
00:31:41,030 --> 00:31:41,890
Pass them back.

780
00:31:46,830 --> 00:31:47,560
Pass them on.

781
00:31:50,030 --> 00:31:52,290
Pay attention. Only after the bell rings

782
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:54,920
can you start answering questions.

783
00:31:58,650 --> 00:31:59,580
The exam begins.

784
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:28,830
I'm back.

785
00:32:29,350 --> 00:32:30,240
Sweetie is back.

786
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,830
How was the exam?

787
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:35,440
It was okay.

788
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:37,640
As long as it's not math,

789
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:38,790
anything is fine.

790
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:42,240
Please, no more math exams.

791
00:32:43,590 --> 00:32:44,450
By the way, Mom.

792
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:46,240
You know what?

793
00:32:47,030 --> 00:32:50,000
Our proctor was so weird.

794
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,330
Instead of proctoring,

795
00:32:51,560 --> 00:32:53,980
he was hiding there reading about UFOs.

796
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:55,550
Your mom didn't ask about your teacher.

797
00:32:55,550 --> 00:32:56,790
She asked how you did on the exam.

798
00:32:56,790 --> 00:32:57,830
I just said.

799
00:32:57,830 --> 00:32:58,750
It was okay.

800
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:02,000
Mock exams don't matter.

801
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:04,570
Your attitude is wrong.

802
00:33:05,790 --> 00:33:06,440
What?

803
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,060
Let me tell you.

804
00:33:08,450 --> 00:33:10,310
This mock exam is very important.

805
00:33:10,440 --> 00:33:12,240
It is a rehearsal for the Gaokao.

806
00:33:13,850 --> 00:33:16,200
Sweetie, your dad was a university student
of the class of 1961-1965.

807
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:18,200
You can't go wrong listening to him.

808
00:33:19,670 --> 00:33:21,730
I want to discuss something with you.

809
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:25,140
I did pretty well on this exam.

810
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:27,170
And I can do well next time, too.

811
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,500
I can do well again.

812
00:33:28,550 --> 00:33:29,070
If so,

813
00:33:29,070 --> 00:33:32,670
can you let me go participate
in the host competition in Beijing?

814
00:33:33,590 --> 00:33:34,350
Let go of me.

815
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:35,830
Save it.

816
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:36,790
Get up.

817
00:33:36,810 --> 00:33:37,620
I'm begging you.

818
00:33:37,620 --> 00:33:39,220
S-Sit properly. Don't move.

819
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:44,330
Hey, at a time like this,

820
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:47,050
can you get your priorities straight?

821
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:48,240
How did I fail to prioritize?

822
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:48,830
I did!

823
00:33:48,830 --> 00:33:50,230
The primary is studying.

824
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:51,550
As for the secondary,

825
00:33:51,550 --> 00:33:52,590
I need to have hobbies, too!

826
00:33:52,590 --> 00:33:54,920
I-I have dreams I want to pursue.

827
00:33:54,940 --> 00:33:55,790
Is that not allowed?

828
00:33:55,790 --> 00:33:57,240
I want to be a host!

829
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:58,070
Why can't I?

830
00:33:58,070 --> 00:33:59,200
Mom, say something!

831
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:02,690
What are you doing, old man?

832
00:34:03,640 --> 00:34:05,030
You should encourage our Sweetie.

833
00:34:05,030 --> 00:34:05,980
Work-life balance.

834
00:34:05,980 --> 00:34:06,510
Exactly.

835
00:34:06,530 --> 00:34:08,280
Listen, she won't get better
with you around.

836
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:09,010
What did I do?

837
00:34:09,030 --> 00:34:09,440
Go.

838
00:34:10,030 --> 00:34:11,020
Okay, okay, I got it.

839
00:34:11,020 --> 00:34:12,280
Go mind your own stuff.

840
00:34:16,030 --> 00:34:17,170
Dad, I'm begging you.

841
00:34:17,170 --> 00:34:18,630
I promise I'll study hard.

842
00:34:19,590 --> 00:34:21,190
Think about it another way.

843
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:23,239
This might become a motivation.

844
00:34:23,510 --> 00:34:25,090
Maybe I'll study even harder

845
00:34:25,090 --> 00:34:26,070
and better,

846
00:34:26,090 --> 00:34:27,900
and get higher grades than before.

847
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:29,429
-I beg you.
-That's enough.

848
00:34:30,710 --> 00:34:31,570
How about this?

849
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,070
If you can get into the top 50

850
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:38,030
in this mock exam,

851
00:34:38,350 --> 00:34:39,480
I might consider it.

852
00:34:42,550 --> 00:34:43,190
Really?

853
00:34:44,710 --> 00:34:46,110
Forty-nine is okay, too?

854
00:34:46,110 --> 00:34:47,920
Dad, how about around 50?

855
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:49,840
Give me some wiggle room.

856
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:52,670
Fifty-five, fifty-four?

857
00:34:53,550 --> 00:34:55,480
Does this count as your agreement?

858
00:34:55,929 --> 00:34:57,160
Dad, did you agree?

859
00:34:57,710 --> 00:34:58,970
I'll take that as a yes.

860
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:00,880
I'm going to study hard then.

861
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:01,590
Don't disturb me.

862
00:35:01,590 --> 00:35:02,850
No eating, no drinking.

863
00:35:02,850 --> 00:35:03,590
Just studying hard.

864
00:35:03,590 --> 00:35:04,850
I'm studying hard now.

865
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:06,900
Are you skipping the meal?

866
00:35:08,910 --> 00:35:09,750
Naughty girl.

867
00:35:11,750 --> 00:35:13,250
Look, it's a mess again.

868
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:14,940
She's just like you, you know?

869
00:35:16,970 --> 00:35:21,230
[Western Tiecheng
Dongfang Affiliated Middle School]

870
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:06,820
What are you doing?

871
00:36:09,190 --> 00:36:10,800
Forget about the exam you just finished.

872
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:11,850
Calm down

873
00:36:11,870 --> 00:36:13,800
and prepare for the last math test.

874
00:36:16,590 --> 00:36:19,630
It's exactly Math that I'm worried about.

875
00:36:20,030 --> 00:36:21,710
My math is already just average.

876
00:36:21,710 --> 00:36:22,880
I wanted to review

877
00:36:22,900 --> 00:36:24,150
formulas yesterday,

878
00:36:24,170 --> 00:36:24,940
but my dad

879
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:26,800
forced me to do more exercises.

880
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:27,470
Great.

881
00:36:27,660 --> 00:36:29,460
Now my mind is completely blank.

882
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:31,630
If I don't get good scores,

883
00:36:31,630 --> 00:36:33,240
my dad will definitely make me apply

884
00:36:33,240 --> 00:36:34,330
for those safe,

885
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:35,890
backup, and boring majors.

886
00:36:37,150 --> 00:36:39,880
Yeah. Then... What are you going to do?

887
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:44,230
Why are you worried?

888
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:47,960
Then...

889
00:36:49,230 --> 00:36:51,110
Doesn't that mean
you'll have to say goodbye

890
00:36:51,110 --> 00:36:52,030
to your artistic dreams?

891
00:36:52,030 --> 00:36:54,230
Why do you appear
even more worried than I am?

892
00:36:54,230 --> 00:36:55,560
Your grades are so good.

893
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:04,440
Xiaoman and I
don't really have any dreams.

894
00:37:06,030 --> 00:37:08,510
Sometimes we see your dreams

895
00:37:08,510 --> 00:37:09,760
as our own.

896
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:15,230
I know Xiaoman has no dreams.

897
00:37:16,180 --> 00:37:17,710
But how can you not have any?

898
00:37:18,230 --> 00:37:19,440
You work so hard.

899
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:25,010
Getting into a good university

900
00:37:25,030 --> 00:37:26,430
and going to a big city...

901
00:37:27,070 --> 00:37:28,670
That's my mom's dream for me.

902
00:37:29,330 --> 00:37:30,210
Well,

903
00:37:30,710 --> 00:37:32,000
you just stay down-to-earth

904
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,110
and study hard.

905
00:37:33,130 --> 00:37:34,440
With your good grades,

906
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:36,970
you'll have a chance
to jump out of this cycle.

907
00:37:37,030 --> 00:37:39,170
I just hope you won't end up
like your dad and me,

908
00:37:39,170 --> 00:37:42,900
who have spent our entire lives
working in the East Chemical Plant.

909
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:51,280
Hearing you say that,

910
00:37:52,230 --> 00:37:54,230
I think I understand my dad a bit now.

911
00:37:55,590 --> 00:37:56,880
The things I do

912
00:37:57,800 --> 00:38:00,700
really aren't what he wants me to do.

913
00:38:14,630 --> 00:38:15,960
I've come up with an idea

914
00:38:16,230 --> 00:38:17,890
to improve your math results.

915
00:38:20,230 --> 00:38:21,010
What is it?

916
00:38:21,130 --> 00:38:24,550
[The subject of this exam: Math]

917
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:10,660
What happened?

918
00:40:15,710 --> 00:40:16,440
Mr. Gu.

919
00:40:17,510 --> 00:40:20,110
Xia Lei and Yan Xiaodan are
both good students.

920
00:40:20,230 --> 00:40:21,440
Could there be a misunderstanding?

921
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:22,280
That's true.

922
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:24,270
If they weren't good students,

923
00:40:24,270 --> 00:40:27,330
they wouldn't have come up
with such a cheating method.

924
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:33,090
What exactly happened?

925
00:40:33,590 --> 00:40:35,870
Did you send a note

926
00:40:35,940 --> 00:40:37,040
or something?

927
00:40:37,070 --> 00:40:38,400
Here. See for yourself.

928
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:42,400
What... What is this?

929
00:40:42,590 --> 00:40:44,120
There's a code on the scale.

930
00:40:44,510 --> 00:40:46,510
Half a centimeter counts as one question.

931
00:40:46,510 --> 00:40:47,960
Where you mark the scale

932
00:40:48,150 --> 00:40:50,030
corresponds to the options.

933
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:52,920
These are your "good students."

934
00:40:54,630 --> 00:40:57,230
Well, I understand the code on the scale.

935
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:59,480
But the marks...

936
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:01,190
Where are they?

937
00:41:01,190 --> 00:41:03,120
Aren't the marks right here? Look.

938
00:41:11,510 --> 00:41:12,870
Mr. Gu, look.

939
00:41:12,900 --> 00:41:13,780
In this case,

940
00:41:14,080 --> 00:41:15,610
it's not convincing.

941
00:41:18,190 --> 00:41:19,250
If this is the case,

942
00:41:20,010 --> 00:41:20,920
just let the two of them explain

943
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:21,780
what happened.

944
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:23,950
All right. Okay.

945
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:27,960
You two, tell me what happened.

946
00:41:29,060 --> 00:41:30,350
This is our own school.

947
00:41:30,650 --> 00:41:32,180
Your teacher is right here.

948
00:41:32,230 --> 00:41:33,160
Don't be afraid.

949
00:41:33,550 --> 00:41:35,080
Just tell us whatever it is.

950
00:41:46,780 --> 00:41:47,780
Mr. Gu, I'm sorry.

951
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:49,720
I-I came up with this terrible idea.

952
00:41:49,720 --> 00:41:51,250
When I passed her the ruler,

953
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:52,460
you caught me. I...

954
00:41:52,550 --> 00:41:54,150
W-We...

955
00:41:54,920 --> 00:41:55,590
We know we were wrong.

956
00:41:55,590 --> 00:41:56,440
We will never do it again.

957
00:41:56,440 --> 00:41:57,360
Please forgive us.

958
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:58,760
Mr. Gu, we were wrong.

959
00:41:58,760 --> 00:41:59,070
I...

960
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:01,070
Please forgive us, Mr. Gu.

961
00:42:01,070 --> 00:42:04,190
I really didn't
see the answers on the ruler.

962
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:12,840
Mr. Gu,

963
00:42:13,390 --> 00:42:14,320
do you think

964
00:42:14,350 --> 00:42:16,210
there's any other way to solve it?

965
00:42:17,230 --> 00:42:18,030
No.

966
00:42:22,150 --> 00:42:23,680
I'll give them zero points.

967
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:24,670
That's the result.
